{title: Broken Down Merry Go Round}
{artist: Jimmy Wakely | Margaret Whiting}
{composer: Written by Arthur Herbert and Fred Stryker}

Recorded by Jimmy Wakely and Margaret Whiting
Written by Arthur Herbert and Fred Stryker
[3/4 time]
[C]You said that you loved me
But it wasn't [G7]long till I found
That you had me riding
A broken down [C]merry [G7]go [C]round
Sweet kisses you gave me
But soon it was [G7]all over town
That you had me riding
A broken down [C]merry [G7]go [C]round
You [F]told me that you would [C]always be near
[G7]Love me my dear through [C]sorrow and tears
But [F]all I've left is a [C]brass souvenir
In[D7]stead of a ring made of [G7]gold
My poor heart is [C]breaking
You've made me a [G7]fool and a clown
